<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-1029 </DOCNO><TEXT>The essay deals with the binding of criminal law on valid permissionsgiven by authorities. Criminal courts are bound on the content of validadministrative acts, even when those are against the law but not invalid.By not considering administrative permissions, criminal courts ignorethe binding force of official acts. They infringe the prohibition notto diverge from a valid act even when the addresse of the act knows thatit is against the law.</TEXT></DOC>